sequenceDiagram                                                       /*EXERCISE 0.5*/
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML document for SPA
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The SPA is loaded, and JavaScript starts

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: JavaScript for SPA
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The SPA JavaScript initializes and fetches data

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: [{ "content": "HTML is easy", "date": "2023-1-1" }, ... ]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The SPA renders the notes using the fetched data

    browser->>browser: User interacts with the SPA (e.g., views and adds notes)
